igenen Erfahrungshorizont verankert werden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aExperience in literature. 0aHolocaust survivors in literature. 0aHolocaust survivors' writings. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945), in literature. 0aMemory in literature. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 4aErfahrung. 4aErzähltheorie. 4aGeneration. 4aKognitive Poetik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831106740260 cprintz978311067386940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311067396840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110673968423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110673968.jpg  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Ebook Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020